HEADWORD: Plant-cane
<hw>Plant"-cane`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stalk or shoot
of sugar cane of the first growth from the cutting. The growth of the
second and following years is of inferior quality, and is called
<xex>rattoon</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

